\pard\f0\fs28 A very variable complex which has been divided into numerous species and subspecies which are, however, ill-defined and appear to represent the more distinct of the numerous isolated populations.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28 The smaller and more isolated of these, particularly towards the edge of the range of the species, are fairly homogeneous, but in other areas there is considerable variation within populations. While it is likely that most populations are statistically separable from one another, there is a large amount of overlap between them and intermediates occur frequently. Two subspecies can be recognized:
